# Sunday Brunch with Giselle - Environment Variables Template
# Copy this file to .env.local for local development

# =============================================================================
# IMPORTANT: Never commit .env or .env.local files to version control!
# Add these to .gitignore to prevent accidental exposure of sensitive data.
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ConvertKit Configuration (Netlify Serverless Functions)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# These variables are used ONLY by the Netlify serverless function
# They should be configured in Netlify UI under Site Settings > Environment Variables
#
# SECURITY: Do NOT prefix these with VITE_ - that would expose them in the client bundle!
# SECURITY: These should ONLY be set in Netlify environment, not in .env files

# Your ConvertKit API Key (found in ConvertKit Account Settings)
# CONVERTKIT_API_KEY=your_api_key_here

# Your ConvertKit Form ID (found in ConvertKit Forms)
# CONVERTKIT_FORM_ID=your_form_id_here

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Supabase Configuration (Sprint 4: User Reviews & Ratings)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Supabase provides backend services: authentication, database, storage
# Get these values from your Supabase project dashboard (Settings > API)
#
# SECURITY: These are PUBLIC keys safe to expose (VITE_ prefix required)
# The anon key has Row Level Security (RLS) policies enforced by Supabase

# Your Supabase project URL (e.g., https://xxxxx.supabase.co)
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_project_url_here

# Your Supabase anonymous/public key (safe to expose, RLS enforced)
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key_here

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Client-Side Environment Variables (Optional)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Variables prefixed with VITE_ are bundled into the client application
# Only use VITE_ prefix for NON-SENSITIVE data that's safe to expose publicly

# Example: Feature flags or public API endpoints
# VITE_ENABLE_ANALYTICS=true
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://api.sundaybrunch.com

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Local Development Notes
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local
# 2. Fill in your ConvertKit credentials
# 3. Run `netlify dev` to test serverless functions locally
# 4. NEVER commit .env.local to git
# 5. For production, set environment variables in Netlify UI

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Netlify CLI Commands
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Test serverless functions locally:
#   npx netlify dev
#
# Test specific function:
#   npx netlify functions:invoke subscribe --payload '{"email":"test@example.com"}'
#
# Deploy to Netlify:
#   git push origin main (triggers automatic deployment)
